documentation.text:
@notice A contract which is the manager for all of the liquidations of the protocol.
LiquidationEngine will be the interface for the liquidator to trigger any positions into the liquidation process.

batchLiquidate(bytes32[],address[],uint2.details: Can only be called by a whitelisted liquidator

params._collateralPoolIds: The ids of the collateral pools for the positions to be liquidated
params._collateralRecipients: The addresses to receive the liquidated collateral
params._debtShareToBeLiquidateds: The amount of debt to be liquidated for each position
params._maxDebtShareToBeLiquidateds: The maximum amount of debt that can be liquidated for each position
params._positionAddresses: The addresses of the positions to be liquidated
params.datas: Extra data to be passed to each liquidation call

blacklist(address).details: Can only be called by the contract owner or the governance system

params.toBeRemoved: The address to be removed from the whitelist

initialize(address,address).details: The function can only be called once after contract deployment

params._bookKeeper: The address of the BookKeeper contract
params._systemDebtEngine: The address of the SystemDebtEngine contract

liquidate(bytes32,address,uint256,uint25.details: Can only be called by a whitelisted liquidator

params._collateralPoolId: The id of the collateral pool for the position to be liquidated
params._collateralRecipient: The address to receive the liquidated collateral
params._data: Extra data to be passed to the liquidation call
params._debtShareToBeLiquidated: The amount of debt to be liquidated
params._maxDebtShareToBeLiquidated: The maximum amount of debt that can be liquidated
params._positionAddress: The address of the position to be liquidated

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

whitelist(address).details: Can only be called by the contract owner or the governance system

blacklist(address).notice: Remove a liquidator from the whitelist

whitelist(address).notice: Add a new liquidator to the whitelist

userdoc.notice: A contract which is the manager for all of the liquidations of the protocol. LiquidationEngine will be the interface for the liquidator to trigger any positions into the liquidation process.
